whereas.text:
Whereas on June 19, 1865, Union soldiers led by Major General Gordon Granger arrived in Galveston,
			 Texas, with news that the Civil War had ended and that the enslaved were
			 free;

Whereas African-Americans who had been slaves in the Southwest celebrated June 19th, commonly known
			 as “Juneteenth Independence Day”, as the anniversary of their
			 emancipation;
